PN,43702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1779981070
OL,3,C'A powerful recognition': Ancient
OL,4,Cmoors gain National Nature Reserve
OL,5,Cstatus
OL,7,FThe creation of this new network
OL,8,Facross Cornwall's distinctive "clay
OL,9,Fcountry" has been described as a
OL,10,F"powerful recognition of the
OL,11,Flandscape's extraordinary natural and
OL,12,Fcultural heritage".
OL,14,FLocated in the heartlands of central
OL,15,FCornwall, with St Austell to the
OL,16,Fsouth, Bodmin to the east, and St
OL,17,FColumb Major to the north, the area
OL,18,Fserves a community living in one of
OL,19,FCornwall's most rurally deprived
OL,20,Fregions.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
