PN,43704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1779981070
OL,3,C'A powerful recognition': Ancient
OL,4,Cmoors gain National Nature Reserve
OL,5,Cstatus
OL,7,FForming a patchwork of semi-natural
OL,8,Fhabitats, the Mid Cornwall Moors are
OL,9,Fhome to rare habitats and species
OL,10,Fincluding wet 'willow carr' woodland,
OL,11,Fwith the rare willow tit, and raised
OL,12,Fbogs with sphagnum moss, lesser
OL,13,Fbutterfly orchid, royal fern and the
OL,14,Fcarnivorous round-leaved sundew.
OL,15,FCornish moneywort, which is unique to
OL,16,FCornwall's tin streaming landscape,
OL,17,Falso thrives.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
